An Act relating to fair compensation for bilingual police officers.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Chapter 41 of the General Laws, as appearing in the 2022 Official Edition,
2 is hereby amended by inserting after Section 108L, the following section:-
3 Section 108MMMM. There is hereby established a language proficiency pay program
4 offering stipends, salary increase or other monetary incentive to regular full-time members of the
5 various city and town police departments who speak one or more languages in addition to
6 English which are also spoken in the communities they serve as compensation for their linguistic
7 proficiency and contribution to the department within that skillset.
8 Police stipends, salary increase or other monetary incentive within this program shall be
9 predicated on the members with linguistic proficiency in relation to a language spoken within the
10 town or city of the police department. The criteria for establishing language proficiency shall
11 include but shall not be limited to: achieving the minimum school of the applicable World
12 Language Assessment Instrument used for the Massachusetts State Seal of Biliteracy or a
